This is the void you have to add:
[code=java]
/**
	 * Herblore - herb identifying
	 */
	public void identifyHerb(int ReqLvl, int exp, int delete, int add, String newHerb) {
		if(playerLevel[5] >= ReqLvl) {
		if (System.currentTimeMillis() - foodDelay < 2000)
			return;
			foodDelay = System.currentTimeMillis();
				sM("You identified the herb as a " + newHerb + ".");
				deleteItem(delete, getItemSlot(delete), 1);
				addItem(add, 1);
				addSkillXP(exp, 5);
			} else {
				sM("You need a herblore level of at least " + ReqLvl + " to identify this herb.");
		} 
	}
[/code]

/****************** The void explained *****************/
identifyHerb is the name of our void, which will be used in our class to make the method under it happen.
then between () are the ints in order how it will be filled in in our lines in the new class, you will understand what I mean when you see them.
then if playerlevel*... is to check if the player has the right level to identify the herb
if it does it checks if there has been some time between the last time he cleaned the herb
then when above 2 are ok, you get the message send that you identified the herb as a (the herb you identified obviously)
it deletes the current un identified herb and adds the new identified herb
adding some skill experience for identifying the herb

then the else statement is when the player didn't have the right level to identify the herb,
it send the player a message which level he needs to do this.
/****************************************************/




